Locked architectural decisions
1. Used only for collections

This schema is never used for single-resource responses.

2. Separate from data

Collection responses follow the pattern:

{
  "data": [
    ...
  ],
  "pagination": {
    ...
  }
}

not

{
  "data": {
    "items": [],
    "pagination": {}
  }
}

This keeps every collection response consistent.

3. Independent of resource type

The same schema is reused for:

Executions
Verifications
Policies
Future collection resources
Canonical Principle (Locked)

Pagination is a reusable metadata object for collection resources only.

It is independent of business resources and provides a consistent navigation model across all paginated Parmana APIs.


{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://schemas.parmana.ai/common/pagination.schema.json",
  "title": "Pagination",
  "description": "Canonical pagination metadata for collection responses.",
  "type": "object",
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "required": [
    "page",
    "pageSize",
    "totalItems",
    "totalPages"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "page": {
      "type": "integer",
      "minimum": 1,
      "description": "Current page number."
    },
    "pageSize": {
      "type": "integer",
      "minimum": 1,
      "description": "Number of items returned per page."
    },
    "totalItems": {
      "type": "integer",
      "minimum": 0,
      "description": "Total number of available items."
    },
    "totalPages": {
      "type": "integer",
      "minimum": 0,
      "description": "Total number of available pages."
    },
    "hasNext": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "description": "Indicates whether another page exists."
    },
    "hasPrevious": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "description": "Indicates whether a previous page exists."
    }
  },
  "examples": [
    {
      "page": 1,
      "pageSize": 25,
      "totalItems": 142,
      "totalPages": 6,
      "hasNext": true,
      "hasPrevious": false
    }
  ]
}